text: A dazzling lineup of artists lit up the stage at the 2022 K-Culture Festival’s “THE-K Concert”! On October 7, the annual K-Culture Festival prepared to wrap up this year’s nine-day run with a star-studded concert at the Seoul Olympic Stadium. The artists who took the stage to perform at the event included NCT DREAM, WINNER, MONSTA X, IVE, Block B’s Zico, STAYC, WJSN, MAX, CRAVITY, MCND, and BLANK2Y. Check out all of the performances from the concert below! NCT DREAM – “Beatbox,” “Hot Sauce,” “Hello Future,” and “Glitch Mode”  WINNER – “REALLY REALLY,” “MILLIONS,” “Empty,” and “I LOVE U”  MONSTA X – “DRAMARAMA,” “Burning Up,” “GAMBLER,” and “ZONE”  IVE – “After LIKE,” “ELEVEN,” and “LOVE DIVE”  Zico – “Freak,” “Artist,” “New thing,” “Okey Dokey,” and “Any Song”  STAYC – “BEAUTIFUL MONSTER” and “RUN2U”  WJSN – “Last Sequence,” “SAVE ME, SAVE YOU,” and “As You Wish”  MAX – “Colour Vision,” “Love Me Less,” “Acid Dreams,” “Blueberry Eyes,” “IT’S YOU” + “Lights Down Low,” and “Mug Shot”  CRAVITY – “PARTY ROCK,” “Boogie Woogie,” and “Adrenaline”  MCND – “#MOOD,” “ICE AGE,” and “Crush”  BLANK2Y – “FUEGO (Fearless),” “Touch,” and “FUEGO (Burn it up)”
title: Watch: Performances From 2022 K-Culture Festival’s THE-K CONCERT | Soompi
